  "text": "For example, the TNFR family member CD40 (TNFRSF5) has been extensively studied as a cell surface receptor; however, it was recently shown to be present not only in the plasma membrane and cytoplasm but also in the nucleus of human normal and lymphoma cell lines [CITATION_1] . Nuclear CD40 interacts with c-Rel, but not with p65, subunits of NF-κB and complexes with c-Rel on the promoters of some NF-κB target genes, thereby enhancing c-Rel-mediated transactivation [CITATION_2] . Thus, the cooperation between nuclear CD40 and c-Rel appears to be important in regulating genes involved in lymphoma cell proliferation and survival [CITATION_3] .",
